<p><strong>Seeking Greenlights:</strong> Yes</p>
<p><strong>Page Type:</strong> SCP Article</p>
<p><strong>Genre (Optional):</strong> Drama, Narrative-driven.</p>
<p><strong>Page Layout (Optional):</strong> As other narrative-driven SCPs, the page will have different iterations of the SCP article.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Elevator Pitch:</strong> A gladius that can transform into a ballet dancing woman-like automaton. It has a host which, when killed, pass the &quot;hosting&quot; to their murder. If the owner was killed in an unintentional way or by a non-humanoid killer, the SCP becomes the protector of its host until it is defeated. SCP is looking to be a &quot;Perfect Weapon&quot; for a &quot;Perfect Warrior&quot;, so it will defend its host from killing attempts turning into the automaton. Also, it keeps and shares every past hosts' warfare skills and some memories, turning the actual host more proficient in combat. Even seemingly useless proficiencies as ballet dancing dexterity can be weaponized by the SCP, turned into a fighting style.</p>
<p><strong>Central Narrative:</strong> The narrative is more centred on the unintentional host that defeated the SCP while retrieving it. They are an common field agent that was in the wrong place at the wrong time. This host will discover SCP “memory flash drive&quot; powers and turned into the subject of an mnestic experiment to discover the SCP memories. First experiments are very positive, revealing previous owners, how the SCP got its abilities and the abilities it gives to the host. The hosts start presenting PTSD signals by living another person's memories even out of the experiments, mainly war memories. Psychological, therapeutic and psychiatric accompaniments start getting more necessary. Amnestics are tried, but as the SCP “reloads” the memories every time, it’s worthless. As more accidents took place, the experiments are ceased. Main directive becomes containing both SCP and host in a chamber as the host’s hyperarousal episodes turn the SCP violent. The Foundation have to repeatedly contain the host from killing themself as their psychological condition is going worse.</p>
<p><strong>Hook/Attention-Grabber:</strong> The host's events are more connected to the Foundation's experiments and protocols than the SCP itself as the mnestics paved the way for this to happen. As the Foundation have to deal with the results of their actions, they tries to keep the host alive in their bad psychological state.</p>
<p><strong>Additional Notes:</strong> I want to know if you think the SCP is weak for being focused on its &quot;owner''. Also, I want to know if the narratives are interesting or if in its anachronic file-based narrative the story will become boring. I'll try to keep with the &quot;Cold, not Cruel&quot; and &quot;Flawed, not Fools&quot; all the time, but I need more critics about it.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><em>As a courtesy to our readers on mobile devices, please collapse long posts. Also, please note the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-13095662/required-reading:how-to-use-this-forum-ideas">Ideas Critique required reading</a> wordcount limit; your post is about 30 words over. Please address this before seeking further feedback. ~Zyn</em></p>

